  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      three hundred morbidly obese patients candidate for sleeve gastrectomy will divided into&#xD;
      equal two groups, group A : will operated by standard sleeve gastrectomy on bougie 36 without&#xD;
      plication of stable line and group B: will operated by sleeve gastrectomy on bougie 42 with&#xD;
      plication of stable line. the aim is to test the effect of pilcation on the incidence of&#xD;
      leaks and bleeding&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      three hundred morbidly obese patients candidate for sleeve gastrectomy will divided into&#xD;
      equal two groups, group A : will operated by standard sleeve gastrectomy on bougie 36 without&#xD;
      plication of stable line and group B: will operated by sleeve gastrectomy on bougie 42 with&#xD;
      plication of stable line. the primary outcomes is the incidence of leaks and bleeding which&#xD;
      is the main nightmare of sleeve gastrectomy, secondary outcome operative time, weight loss&#xD;
      and metabolic effect&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
